1
00:00:00,970 --> 00:00:03,510
(Episode 120)

2
00:00:05,780 --> 00:00:06,780
The sample has been collected.

3
00:00:07,210 --> 00:00:10,950
I'll take it to the DNA lab right away
and request a VVIP rush.

4
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:12,220
Wait a minute.

5
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:28,130
I had some hot coffee right before this,

6
00:00:28,630 --> 00:00:32,270
so I'm worried my epithelial cells
weren't collected properly.

7
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:37,110
We can't afford any mistakes.
Let's just redo my sample.

8
00:00:42,650 --> 00:00:44,680
I'll rinse my mouth with water.
I'll be right back.

9
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,130
Kang Hyuk, are you ready?

10
00:01:03,870 --> 00:01:08,670
Chairman Ma is making me give a DNA sample
right in front of him.

11
00:01:08,870 --> 00:01:12,310
- Yes, I'm standing by.
- I came out here to buy some time,

12
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:16,080
so get Jung Suk Hee's sample ready.
And don't mess this up.

13
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:17,320
Understood.

14
00:01:17,980 --> 00:01:20,890
- Call me as soon as the test is done.
- Okay, got it.

15
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:25,060
This has to work.

16
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:27,890
If this goes wrong, it's all over.

17
00:01:42,610 --> 00:01:47,410
I rinsed with plain water,
so we'll get a more accurate sample now.

18
00:02:06,630 --> 00:02:09,730
The code is zero-seven-zero.
Start the operation now.

19
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:12,040
Yes, I'm ready.

20
00:02:14,010 --> 00:02:16,570
From now on, I'm not Chae Hwa Young.
I'm living as Ma Eun Hye.

21
00:02:17,380 --> 00:02:19,410
As the rightful owner of Dream.

22
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:37,960
Honey?

23
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:42,000
What are you talking about?

24
00:02:42,970 --> 00:02:44,300
What do you mean our Ji Hun is missing?

25
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:47,970
Where could he have gone?
Did you call the police?

26
00:02:49,070 --> 00:02:51,680
Hey! You can't just park like that!

27
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:54,410
I was just about to call them.

28
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:58,220
He was gone in the blink of an eye.
What do we do, honey?

29
00:03:06,790 --> 00:03:10,090
I'm in a real emergency.

30
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:11,500
Here's my card. Please call me later.

31
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,000
Forget it. Let's go to the police station.

32
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:15,900
- I said, let's go to the police station.
- Sir, please let go of me.

33
00:03:15,970 --> 00:03:18,300
Let go? Are you kidding?
I said let's go to the police station.

34
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:19,700
Didn't you hear me?

35
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,710
- I really have to...
- I said, let's go!

36
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,440
- It's a real emergency...
- You think you're the only one in a rush?

37
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:26,240
So am I. Let's go to the police station.

38
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:28,110
You're the one who parked like an idiot.

39
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:31,180
- Please calm down.
- Let's go!

40
00:03:31,450 --> 00:03:34,820
Are you deaf or something?
Come on, I said let's go!

41
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:37,760
Let go? No way.
We're going to the police station.

42
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:40,120
Why would I let go?

43
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,460
Come on, let's go!

44
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:47,930
I'm busy too! Let's go.
You can't just park like this.

45
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,230
Let's go to the police station.

46
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,000
What were you thinking, parking like this?

47
00:04:02,310 --> 00:04:03,310
How did it go?

48
00:04:04,380 --> 00:04:06,880
Did you manage to switch my sample
with Jung Suk Hee's?

49
00:04:09,050 --> 00:04:10,320
Good work, Manager Lee.

50
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:12,760
I knew I could count on you.

51
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:20,060
Besides, Secretary Kim was very distracted
when it happened.

52
00:04:20,330 --> 00:04:23,130
He won't even realize
the DNA sample was swapped.

53
00:04:23,970 --> 00:04:27,340
Even if he did find out,
could he really admit it?

54
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:30,610
It's a life-altering mistake.

55
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,090
Now, everything is perfect.

56
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:49,760
What?

57
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:52,060
The nurse from Seo Rin's surgery
is missing?

58
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:53,300
Yes.

59
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:55,100
When I was reviewing the CCTV footage,

60
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:57,940
I noticed she was wearing a smartwatch.

61
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:01,840
So I contacted her,
but she denied remembering anything.

62
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:04,610
That was suspicious, so I looked into it.

63
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:07,180
I found out she was in a relationship
with the surgeon.

64
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:10,480
So they're all in on it together.

65
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:15,490
Then maybe there's a clue
recorded on that smartwatch?

66
00:05:15,550 --> 00:05:16,820
That's exactly what I was thinking.

67
00:05:17,290 --> 00:05:20,430
What if the surgeon
recorded something on it...

68
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:21,660
as an insurance policy?

69
00:05:21,930 --> 00:05:25,200
In case Chae Hwa Young tried
to pin everything on him.

70
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,830
Exactly. Just in case.

71
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:28,830
It'd be too risky for him,

72
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:31,270
so I'm thinking
he had his mistress make the recording.

73
00:05:31,870 --> 00:05:34,140
So when I started pressing her on that...

74
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:35,840
The woman vanished.

75
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:40,340
Yes. I'm sure there's a recording
on that smartwatch.

76
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,210
We need to find out what's on it.

77
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:44,720
Sounds good.

78
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,390
I'll uncover the truth of Seo Rin's death,
no matter what it takes.

79
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:51,560
I still don't understand...

80
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:54,690
why I have to do a DNA test with you.

81
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:58,900
You weren't an orphan, were you?

82
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:02,730
As I recall, I heard you had parents.

83
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:06,340
They've passed away now,
but I did have parents.

84
00:06:07,810 --> 00:06:10,440
It's thanks to the people
who adopted me...

85
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:14,050
that I was given the name Chae Hwa Young.

86
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:15,280
Wait,

87
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,950
so you're saying you were an orphan?

88
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:20,590
Then...

89
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,390
why did you hide that from me?

90
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:26,460
Because I loved Dong Seok so much,

91
00:06:26,790 --> 00:06:30,290
I felt I had no choice but to hide it.

92
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:32,430
Unbelievable.

93
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:39,270
Anyway, the DNA test results
will be out tomorrow,

94
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:42,070
so let's talk then.

95
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:57,420
My gosh, what is going on?

96
00:06:57,420 --> 00:06:58,460
No way.

97
00:06:59,490 --> 00:07:02,690
So that means Chae Hwa Young
is my husband's biological daughter.

98
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:06,400
No way! That can't be happening.

99
00:07:07,130 --> 00:07:11,270
But wait, something
must have added up for them...

100
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:13,440
to get a DNA test, right?

101
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:15,310
Seriously!

102
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:18,980
Oh my goodness.

103
00:07:19,610 --> 00:07:20,610
What?

104
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:24,350
Yes, honey. Why are you calling from home?

105
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:30,520
Let me make one thing perfectly clear.

106
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,720
Whatever happens in this house...

107
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,690
must not leave these walls.

108
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,100
Yes, of course.

109
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:43,770
And this ridiculous nonsense
about CEO Chae being my daughter...

110
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:47,210
Don't you dare go gossiping about it
to anyone in this house.

111
00:07:47,670 --> 00:07:48,670
Got it?

112
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:51,610
Yes, of course.

113
00:07:52,140 --> 00:07:54,510
You know my lips are sealed.

114
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:56,710
If anyone else finds out,

115
00:07:57,220 --> 00:07:59,280
I'll know it was you who blabbed,

116
00:07:59,780 --> 00:08:01,550
and I will never forgive you.

117
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:03,520
So watch your mouth.

118
00:08:03,890 --> 00:08:05,990
- Got it?
- Of course.

119
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:12,500
(Even Hatred is Your Talent)

120
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:19,100
What do you think you're doing?

121
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:21,110
What does it look like?

122
00:08:21,510 --> 00:08:23,010
I'm reading.

123
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:26,180
Is losing 30 million dollars
really hitting her that hard?

124
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:30,850
She'd have a conniption if she knew
I'm the one who has it.

125
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:34,620
What is it? Do you have something to say?

126
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:36,390
What about your promise?

127
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,260
You have to keep your promises.

128
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:39,390
A promise?

129
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:41,560
What promise did I make?

130
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:44,530
You promised to resign...

131
00:08:44,530 --> 00:08:47,030
if you upset Chairman Ali
and she went to another hotel.

132
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:51,470
Chairman Ali never went to another hotel.
She went to another country, didn't she?

133
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:54,010
It's because you upset Chairman Ali...

134
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:56,610
that she canceled the rest
of her trip and left.

135
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:59,410
- How will you make up for this loss?
- Shut up.

136
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,750
Submit a plan tomorrow...

137
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:03,680
on how you'll attract future VVIP clients.

138
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:07,650
Who do you think you are,
lecturing me and telling me what to do?

139
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:11,190
- So what if we lost Chairman Ali?
- What gives you the right to talk so big?

140
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,360
What makes you so full of hot air?

141
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:17,430
You'll see soon enough
whether I'm bluffing or not.

142
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:19,760
Go ahead, run your mouth
while you still can.

143
00:09:20,430 --> 00:09:22,630
Because it won't be long before
you're on your knees,

144
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:24,540
begging me for mercy.

145
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:27,840
- What?
- You're disturbing my reading. Get out.

146
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:39,150
Chae Hwa Young lost 30 million dollars,

147
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,090
so where is all this sudden confidence
coming from?

148
00:09:41,690 --> 00:09:43,720
What on earth is she plotting?

149
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,960
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

150
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:56,870
Chairman Ma said...

151
00:09:57,600 --> 00:10:00,400
when CEO Chae was pregnant with her son,

152
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:02,670
he sent her a golden toad as a gift.

153
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:06,980
Does she still have it?

154
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,550
Why did Baek Ho ask about that?

155
00:10:11,380 --> 00:10:13,080
And why did Manager Lee look so shocked?

156
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:16,990
So Chae Hwa Young left me
and was carrying Chairman Ma's grandchild?

157
00:10:19,060 --> 00:10:20,390
And the baby was a boy?

158
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:23,790
But she said she lost the baby
because of Jang Mi's mother.

159
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,060
The golden toad...

160
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:31,400
He said it's engraved
with his family's unique crest.

161
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:34,840
But why did Baek Ho ask about that?

162
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:36,710
Why?

163
00:10:39,010 --> 00:10:40,240
Kang Hyuk.

164
00:10:40,910 --> 00:10:42,150
What brings you here?

165
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:44,550
I came alone.

166
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:47,790
Don't tell me you came here
to give me a hard time.

167
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:51,990
For publicly humiliating
the Chae Hwa Young you love?

168
00:10:51,990 --> 00:10:53,490
No, of course not.

169
00:10:54,830 --> 00:10:57,060
Have a seat. I'll get you some tea.

170
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:58,130
All right.

171
00:11:00,530 --> 00:11:01,630
Oh dear.

172
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:05,300
Sorry, this is an important client.

173
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,670
No problem, you should get that.

174
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:08,940
I'll just have a look around while I wait.

175
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,240
Okay.

176
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:44,440
Director! I can't believe it.

177
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,210
Do you have any idea
how long I've been looking for you?

178
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:52,080
You remember me, don't you?
It's Han Young Ja.

179
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:55,150
Of course. You were a very generous donor
to our orphanage.

180
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:57,660
- How could I possibly forget you?
- Goodness.

181
00:11:58,090 --> 00:12:02,030
But why have you been out of touch
for so long?

182
00:12:02,430 --> 00:12:05,700
I've been away, recuperating.
I was very ill.

183
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:07,830
Are you feeling better now?

184
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,300
Yes, I'm all better now.

185
00:12:11,370 --> 00:12:13,670
The orphanage went through a series
of mergers and consolidations,

186
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:15,770
and all of the old documents were lost
in the process.

187
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:17,740
So it was hard to find
anyone's contact information.

188
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:21,180
But it must be fate
that we've managed to get in touch again.

189
00:12:21,350 --> 00:12:22,810
Fate, you say?

190
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,750
Fate?

191
00:12:30,420 --> 00:12:32,790
(Ma)

192
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:35,730
This is...

193
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:38,660
What do you mean by fate?

194
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:40,800
What are you trying to say?

195
00:12:40,970 --> 00:12:43,730
I mean your adopted son.

196
00:12:43,730 --> 00:12:45,040
What about Baek Ho?

197
00:12:45,570 --> 00:12:46,570
Do you know...

198
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:50,170
who Baek Ho's birth parents are?

199
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:57,310
Manager Lee?

200
00:12:57,850 --> 00:12:58,880
Where are you?

201
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:00,850
Kang Hyuk!

202
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:05,760
Goodness.

203
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:07,960
Kang Hyuk, what are you doing in here?

204
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:11,260
I found an interesting book
and got caught up reading.

205
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,270
I should get going now.

206
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:18,500
No, wait. At least stay for some tea.

207
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,900
That's all right. Maybe next time.

208
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:21,640
Bye.

209
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:23,110
Bye.

210
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:38,760
(Ma)

211
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:41,690
Lee Kang Hyuk.

212
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:44,360
What was he really looking for?

213
00:13:49,730 --> 00:13:52,900
Why does Kang Baek Ho
have that golden toad?

214
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,270
Is he really that child?

215
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:00,110
How has the Chairman been lately?

216
00:14:02,350 --> 00:14:05,350
I'm worried about him.
He hasn't been looking well at all.

217
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:09,190
Do you think it has something to do
with his daughter?

218
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:12,620
Is someone harassing the Chairman again,
claiming to be his daughter?

219
00:14:14,230 --> 00:14:15,230
Well...

220
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:21,600
We're screening for things like that,
so I don't think that's it.

221
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:25,670
By the way, Baek Ho,
are there any updates...

222
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,610
about the search for your birth parents?

223
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:29,810
Nothing yet.

224
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:33,180
My mom said she'd find the director
of the orphanage and get back to me,

225
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,410
but I guess she hasn't been able
to reach him yet.

226
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,480
The director must know a lot
about your birth parents.

227
00:14:38,780 --> 00:14:41,950
I'm not sure. To be honest,
I'm not sure what's going on myself.

228
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:48,430
I'm sure your parents
are warm and wonderful people.

229
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:50,390
What makes you say that?

230
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:54,270
I can tell by looking at you.
Some things are just in your nature.

231
00:14:55,200 --> 00:15:00,440
I'm sure they're warm and generous,
just good-hearted people.

232
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:03,510
No, it can't be...

233
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:06,280
Just because CEO Chae
has the golden toad...

234
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:08,050
doesn't mean it's related to me.

235
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:09,680
It has to be that way.

236
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,320
Baek Ho, look at this.

237
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:17,790
What's this?

238
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:20,060
You know the Angel Forest Orphanage
where you were as a baby, right?

239
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:24,060
I miraculously got hold of the director
this afternoon.

240
00:15:24,430 --> 00:15:26,160
You mean the orphanage I was adopted from?

241
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:28,700
So you finally got hold of the director?

242
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:29,770
That's right.

243
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:31,840
He said he really wants to see you.

244
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:33,970
It sounded like he has something
to tell you.

245
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:45,880
I'm just here to confirm it.

246
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:51,320
To see if Kang Baek Ho is really the son
of Ma Dong Seok and Chae Hwa Young.

247
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:55,030
To see if he's definitely the child
I abandoned.

248
00:15:56,860 --> 00:15:58,000
I'm just here to make sure.

249
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:08,410
Hey, Jang Mi.

250
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:10,840
I just got to the orphanage.

251
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:14,010
You should have let me come with you.
Why did you go alone?

252
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:15,980
It's not like I'm meeting my parents
or anything.

253
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:20,580
Just like I lean on you,
I want you to be able to lean on me too.

254
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:24,620
I want to be the first person
you turn to for anything.

255
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:29,030
But I lean on you
so much more than you lean on me.

256
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:30,760
I'm serious.

257
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:33,430
It really upsets me
when you go through things alone.

258
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,630
Okay, I get it.

259
00:16:35,070 --> 00:16:37,270
From now on, I'll tell you everything.

260
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,470
That's a promise.

261
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:39,800
Okay?

262
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:41,270
Yes.

263
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:42,340
Okay.

264
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:46,110
No way. Kang Baek Ho...

265
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,710
Is he about to find out everything?

266
00:16:49,310 --> 00:16:52,050
That he's the son of Chae Hwa Young
and Ma Dong Seok.

267
00:16:52,980 --> 00:16:54,150
No way.

268
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,390
Not yet.

269
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:06,260
Hwa Young. What is it?

270
00:17:06,260 --> 00:17:08,830
Where are you? I'm a nervous wreck.

271
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,340
I know what the result will be,
but there's always that "what if."

272
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:16,110
The DNA test results
will arrive any minute.

273
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:19,580
I have to open them with you,
so where are you? Get here now.

274
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:23,950
You're sure nothing went wrong?

275
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,280
Yes, sir.

276
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:28,890
I personally delivered the samples,

277
00:17:29,550 --> 00:17:32,420
and I picked up the results myself.

278
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:38,660
You're sure Chae Hwa Young
didn't try to pull anything?

279
00:17:38,930 --> 00:17:41,270
I went to the lab
you secretly arranged, sir.

280
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:43,630
It's a facility
CEO Chae knows nothing about.

281
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:47,540
I also personally watched
the samples go into the lab.

282
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:53,080
I'm too nervous to look.

283
00:17:54,780 --> 00:17:57,050
What if she's my daughter?

284
00:17:58,780 --> 00:18:02,120
How am I supposed to accept
Chae Hwa Young as my own daughter?

285
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:05,190
But, sir, she's the daughter
you've missed your entire life.

286
00:18:11,630 --> 00:18:14,230
(Prime DNA Center)

287
00:18:16,270 --> 00:18:17,270
(DNA Analysis Results)

288
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:18,800
(Match)

289
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:21,510
(The probability of parentage
between Subjects A and B...)

290
00:18:21,510 --> 00:18:23,010
(is over 99.999 percent.)

291
00:18:23,010 --> 00:18:24,680
(A biological parent-child relationship
is hereby confirmed.)

292
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:30,150
Sir.

293
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:31,550
No.

294
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,180
This can't be true!

295
00:18:34,850 --> 00:18:36,250
This is impossible!

296
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:40,020
This can't be happening.

297
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:54,540
Tae Pyung, we need to get some information
out of the twisted donut lady.

298
00:18:54,770 --> 00:18:57,170
Right, Mom. Let's gather some intel.

299
00:18:57,980 --> 00:18:59,010
Operation begins.

300
00:19:02,210 --> 00:19:03,210
San Wol.

301
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:07,180
How is the Chairman doing?

302
00:19:07,450 --> 00:19:13,160
Goodness.
I love it when you say my name, Tae Pyung.

303
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:16,960
I'm taking great care of the Chairman,
you know.

304
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:20,730
Believe me, I'm getting him everything
that's good for him.

305
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,430
Suk Hee's side dishes are delicious.

306
00:19:22,430 --> 00:19:24,870
Grandfather loves Suk Hee's food.

307
00:19:24,940 --> 00:19:28,510
I know you're a good cook, Suk Hee.

308
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:34,210
But for today, would you mind
giving us some privacy?

309
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:38,680
I'd like some time alone with Tae Pyung.

310
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:43,990
I can't stand her.

311
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:48,260
Twisted donut old lady,
you look pretty today.

312
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:51,090
No, I mean, Ms. Twisted Donut.

313
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:53,030
You're pretty.

314
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:58,600
Well, you're finally saying something
that makes sense.

315
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:03,640
So, San Wol,
has Chae Hwa Young been bothering you?

316
00:20:03,870 --> 00:20:04,940
Goodness.

317
00:20:05,510 --> 00:20:09,580
Just thinking about Chae Hwa Young
makes my blood boil.

318
00:20:10,050 --> 00:20:11,480
Do you know
what she's trying to pull right now...

319
00:20:11,550 --> 00:20:14,320
Trying to pull? What is she scheming now?

320
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:15,920
Well, the thing is...

321
00:20:16,550 --> 00:20:17,990
Will you shut your mouth?

322
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:26,960
They say broccoli is good for health.

323
00:20:28,130 --> 00:20:29,300
Don't you have any?

324
00:20:29,670 --> 00:20:30,730
Broccoli?

325
00:20:32,370 --> 00:20:36,670
I'd love to dip it in some hot sauce
and just crunch it to pieces.

326
00:20:42,450 --> 00:20:43,910
Wait...

327
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,120
What was she about to tell me?

328
00:20:52,490 --> 00:20:55,830
Secretary Kim.
I heard Father asked to see me.

329
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:58,760
Yes. The DNA test results are in.

330
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,500
Hold on.

331
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,400
I'm so nervous...

332
00:21:04,030 --> 00:21:05,540
I can't possibly hear it just like this.

333
00:21:05,740 --> 00:21:07,940
I'd rather have some tea with Father...

334
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:09,870
and take my time hearing the news.

335
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:31,730
Goodness, it's hot!

336
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:43,810
Are you really...

337
00:21:45,580 --> 00:21:46,640
Eun Hye?

338
00:21:55,990 --> 00:21:58,990
"The probability of parentage
between Subjects A and B..."

339
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:02,360
"is over 99.999 percent."

340
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:06,200
"Genetically,
between the aforementioned subjects,"

341
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:11,270
"a biological parent-child relationship
has been established..."

342
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:14,300
"and is hereby confirmed."

343
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:20,740
Then does this mean
I'm really your daughter, Father?

344
00:22:21,410 --> 00:22:23,880
I'm Ma Eun Hye?

345
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,880
How can this be?

346
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,320
Are you really...

347
00:22:29,390 --> 00:22:31,820
my dad? Is that true?

348
00:22:32,890 --> 00:22:34,860
I can't believe it myself.

349
00:22:36,460 --> 00:22:38,160
The test says you're my daughter,

350
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,470
but I can't bring myself to happily...

351
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:44,970
accept you as my own.

352
00:22:46,940 --> 00:22:48,270
But my DNA...

353
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:51,510
Dad.

354
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:56,410
Am I really your daughter, Ma Eun Hye?

355
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:59,120
Are you really my dad?

356
00:23:02,650 --> 00:23:03,820
Well...

357
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,960
That's what the DNA says.

358
00:23:10,230 --> 00:23:11,230
Dad.

359
00:23:12,130 --> 00:23:14,900
To think you were right here all along,
and I never knew...

360
00:23:16,670 --> 00:23:17,670
Dad.

361
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:22,870
This is where
all my acting practice pays off.

362
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:35,620
What's gotten into you?

363
00:23:36,350 --> 00:23:37,350
I...

364
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:40,620
have lived my life all wrong.

365
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,760
As your daughter,

366
00:23:44,330 --> 00:23:47,560
I'm so sorry
for all the terrible things I've done.

367
00:23:49,530 --> 00:23:52,500
But if I can explain,
I had no other choice.

368
00:23:53,170 --> 00:23:55,570
I was abused for being an orphan,
and I grew up poor,

369
00:23:56,670 --> 00:23:59,380
so I couldn't get the education
I dreamed of.

370
00:24:01,110 --> 00:24:06,750
People scorned and hurt me,

371
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:08,450
and it forced me to become ruthless.

372
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,650
Otherwise,

373
00:24:10,690 --> 00:24:13,860
I wouldn't have survived.
It was the only way I could live.

374
00:24:15,790 --> 00:24:18,260
Please forgive me...

375
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:21,830
for not being able to live...

376
00:24:23,270 --> 00:24:24,430
any other way. I'm sorry.

377
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:28,100
I was wrong, Dad.

378
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:31,740
I see.

379
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:33,980
I think I can understand,

380
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:37,250
to some extent,
the life you've had to live.

381
00:24:39,780 --> 00:24:41,850
To survive those harsh years,

382
00:24:42,850 --> 00:24:45,260
you probably had no choice
but to live that way.

383
00:24:46,420 --> 00:24:48,430
If only I had found you sooner,

384
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,630
your life would have turned out
differently.

385
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,230
I am truly sorry.

386
00:24:54,630 --> 00:24:58,170
I'm so sorry that this is the Ma Eun Hye
I've become.

387
00:25:02,540 --> 00:25:07,140
What's with this old geezer?
He's not falling for my brilliant acting.

388
00:25:07,940 --> 00:25:10,250
Does he still not believe
I'm his daughter?

389
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:19,220
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

390
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:22,990
(Shareholder Information,
Choi Ha Joon, Ma Dae Chang)

391
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:24,060
Choi Ha Joon?

392
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:25,700
Born in 1993?

393
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:30,100
Dad.

394
00:25:30,630 --> 00:25:33,000
Does that mean
Dong Seok and I are siblings?

395
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,340
My gosh.

396
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:39,080
What have I done? This is insane.

397
00:25:41,210 --> 00:25:43,380
- But...
- If word of this gets out,

398
00:25:43,910 --> 00:25:48,490
you and Dream Group will be scorned
for the rest of our lives.

399
00:25:49,190 --> 00:25:50,220
Wait, that's...

400
00:25:55,090 --> 00:25:56,090
I don't want to be...

401
00:25:57,690 --> 00:25:59,200
a burden to you.

402
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:02,700
I don't want to be a daughter
who only causes you harm.

403
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,770
I'll be the one to leave.

404
00:26:07,670 --> 00:26:09,070
I'll just quietly...

405
00:26:11,070 --> 00:26:12,440
walk out of this house.

406
00:26:15,010 --> 00:26:16,010
Dong Seok...

407
00:26:16,810 --> 00:26:18,150
is not my biological son.

408
00:26:19,780 --> 00:26:20,780
What?

409
00:26:21,950 --> 00:26:23,990
You're saying Dong Seok isn't your son?

410
00:26:24,490 --> 00:26:25,490
That's right.

411
00:26:27,390 --> 00:26:30,330
I always felt
that losing my wife and daughter...

412
00:26:31,190 --> 00:26:34,400
was entirely my fault.

413
00:26:35,030 --> 00:26:37,800
So I never wanted to go through
the horrible pain...

414
00:26:38,230 --> 00:26:40,540
of losing my family because of me again.

415
00:26:41,270 --> 00:26:43,110
That's why I've lived alone my whole life.

416
00:26:43,370 --> 00:26:45,640
But after pouring your life
into Dream Group,

417
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:49,180
you must have needed a successor, right?

418
00:26:49,780 --> 00:26:53,820
Right. That's why I adopted Dong Seok.

419
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:55,620
In any case,

420
00:26:56,620 --> 00:26:59,020
though we share no blood,

421
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:01,930
he's a son I've loved...

422
00:27:02,860 --> 00:27:04,360
as my own flesh and blood.

423
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:08,100
That's why I doted on the twins so much.

424
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:16,610
The nanny who left you at the orphanage
came to see me.

425
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:18,340
And she said that...

426
00:27:18,710 --> 00:27:22,680
your grandfather died
saving you from a fire,

427
00:27:22,910 --> 00:27:24,410
right after you turned one.

428
00:27:24,850 --> 00:27:28,990
Grandfather died saving me?
What kind of fire was it?

429
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:35,930
(Busin Daily)

430
00:27:35,930 --> 00:27:37,230
("Blaze tears through
Sogong-dong residential area.")

431
00:27:37,290 --> 00:27:38,560
("Homeowner dies,
young grandson miraculously rescued.")

432
00:27:39,060 --> 00:27:41,930
Your real name is Choi Ha Joon.

433
00:27:41,930 --> 00:27:43,300
Choi Ha Joon.

434
00:27:46,500 --> 00:27:47,500
"Choi Ha Joon?"

435
00:27:48,070 --> 00:27:49,340
Born in 1993?

436
00:27:50,470 --> 00:27:53,110
A young punk like him
is the majority shareholder?

437
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:23,110
(The First Man)

438
00:28:23,470 --> 00:28:26,180
Both Baek Ho and CEO Chae
have the grapefruit allergy.

439
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:28,310
Does that mean Baek Ho is CEO Chae's son?

440
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:31,410
Baek Ho has the golden toad.

441
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:33,520
And Baek Ho was also adopted.

442
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:36,350
He's not your son, is he?

443
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:40,190
Seong Hye. It's been a while.
How have you been?

444
00:28:40,460 --> 00:28:41,690
Is that really true?

445
00:28:42,430 --> 00:28:47,160
Are you saying Jung Suk Hee
has Seong Sil's habit?

446
00:28:49,070 --> 00:28:51,070
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
